          "body": "The New Testament treats Christ as the wisdom of God (1 Corinthians 1:24, 30), the one in whom *are hidden all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge* (Colossians 2:3). Colossians 1:15-17 calls Him *the firstborn of all creation* — by Him all things were created — language that consciously draws on Proverbs 8:22-31. John 1:1-3 says the Word was *in the beginning*, *with God*, and that *all things came into being through Him*. These resonances are real, but they must be read carefully. The orthodox reading is not that Proverbs 8 directly predicts Christ as a separate hypostasis (the personification is literary, not Trinitarian metaphysics) — but that the personified Wisdom of Proverbs 8 finds her true and ultimate referent in Christ, in whom the wisdom by which God created and orders the world becomes incarnate. To watch daily at Wisdom's gates is, for the New Testament believer, to watch daily for the Christ in whom that Wisdom dwells bodily."
